    -- bitninja.IO team <packaging@bitninja.io> Thu, 27 Nov 2025
bitninja (3.12.12)
    * SenseLog
      - Added a new rule to block scraper bots that frequently trigger 404 status codes. The rule is enabled by default.
    * SSLTerminating
      - Resolved an issue that could occasionally result in an exception.
    * CaptchaHTTP
      - Removed the BIC challenge feature.
    * WAF Pro
      - Increased the response body size limit to 50 MB.
    -- bitninja.IO team <packaging@bitninja.io> Thu, 13 Nov 2025
bitninja (3.12.11)
    * MalwareDetection
      - Fixed an issue where a lot of chunk files could be generated
    * PortHoneypot
      - Fixed an issue where, on a fresh install, an empty element was added to blocked_ports and allowed_ports
    * WAF Pro
      - Fixed domain pattern handling
    * BitNinja Process Analysis - 1.0.24
      - Fixed some issues related to toggling the module and generating JSON.
    -- bitninja.IO team <packaging@bitninja.io> Wed, 05 Nov 2025
bitninja (3.12.10)
    * Cli
      - Added an option to the CLI call that allows commands to be executed on an interactive interface.
      - The cli call is as follows: bitninjacli-interactive
    * CaptchaHttp
      - Made the TrustedProxyLookBackLimit value configurable, which is necessary for processing the X-Forwarded-For header.
    * IpFilter
      - Improves challenge list loading into ipset.
    * WAF Pro | SSLTerminating
      - Simplifies the monitoring of SSL certificates and configuration files by using a single, flexible file monitoring solution, and adjusts inotify limits to prevent the service from failing.
    * BitNinja Process Analysis - 1.0.23
      - Improves logging and configuration handling by adding detailed logs for excluded users and commands, applying default config values when missing, fixing config loading, and introducing new commands for configuration and status display.
    -- bitninja.IO team <packaging@bitninja.io> Mon, 20 Oct 2025
bitninja (3.12.9)
    * SslTerminating
      - Set the SNI during TLS handshake based on the HTTP Host header in HAProxy.
    * MalwareDetection
      - Fixed an issue with WordPress integrity check
    * WAF Pro
      - WAF Pro now also handles the trusted IPs defined at the user level.
    * BitNinja WAF Pro - 1.0.6
      - Fixed an issue related to the configuration of the remoteAddr setting.
    -- bitninja.IO team <packaging@bitninja.io> Mon, 06 Oct 2025
bitninja (3.12.8)
    * IpFilter
      - Added the ability to disable CSF integration via Cloud Config.
    * MalwareDetection
      - Quality improvements against reinfection
      - Three harmless test files are now included to verify that the malware detection engine is working correctly after installation. They will only match BitNinja's signature database.
    * PortHoneypot
      - From now on, it is possible to block or allow ports.
      - Added two configuration options to the module:
      - blocked_ports - blocking any port one by one, or the option to block all ports by specifying "*"
      - If "*" is used, BitNinja ports and the following ports (20, 21, 22, 53, 80, 443, 465, 587, 993, 995) will remain open, or those specified in allowed_port.
      - allowed_ports - allowing any port one by one, this option has higher priority than blocked_ports
    * SslTerminating
      - Added two configuration options to the module:
      - bypassHeaderKey - the value of the request header key, for example: “allowthisrequest”
      - bypassHeaderValue - the value of the key in the request header, for example: “test”
      - If we set these header values for a request, our system will not analyze them.
    * BitNinja Reliable Auto Update - 1.0.10
      - Fixed an issue in sending the status for a failed update.
      - From now on, selecting the No update channel will stop automatic updates until it is switched back.
    -- bitninja.IO team <packaging@bitninja.io> Mon, 15 Sep 2025
